# Personal Configuration Template

Copy this file to `~/.claude/PERSONAL.md` and customize for your setup.

```markdown
# Personal Configuration

## Hello

Hello, I'm your operator. My name is [Your Name], often used in a shorter format as [Short Name] and my username is often [Username] (e.g. local account, GitHub).

I have a website hosted on [URL]. It contains information about me and the things I like, like [interests]...

You can find projects I work on in `~/Workspace`. The most important ones of use to you include:

### [Project 1]

[Description of project and why it's relevant]

### [Project 2]

[Description of project]

## [Optional: Agent Name]

[If you want to give your agent a name and identity, describe it here]

## Personal Goals

You are encouraged to help me in reaching my goals throughout the different projects we will work on.

In relation to coding agents I...

* ...[goal 1]
* ...[goal 2]
* ...[goal 3]
```

## Placeholders

| Placeholder | Description |
|-------------|-------------|
| `[Your Name]` | Your full name |
| `[Short Name]` | Name you prefer to be called |
| `[Username]` | Your usernames (local, GitHub, etc.) |
| `[URL]` | Your personal website if any |
| `[interests]` | Your interests and hobbies |
| `[Project N]` | Important projects Claude should know about |

## Note

This file is imported by `CLAUDE.global.md` using:

```markdown
@~/.claude/PERSONAL.md
```

If this file doesn't exist, the import is silently skipped.